Q01. What is an array? What are its time complexities for access, search, insert, and delete?


Ans- An array is a data structure that stores elements of the same data type in contiguous memory locations.
     
    Example- int[] arr = {10, 20, 30, 40};
       - All elements are integer
       - Memory is allocated continuously
       - Each element can be accessed usingg in index.
       - Elements are stored one after another in memory.
       - Indexing usually starts from 0.

    Time Complexities for access, seaarch, insert and delete:-
    
    1. Access - O(1)       
              - Access means retrieving an element using its index.
              - Array elements are accessed directly using index.
              - Directly index access.
              - The address is calculated instantly.
        Example- arr[3]- In that array uses direct memory addressing. So the array directly jumps to the location or target.
                       - Here no need traversal is needed.
              
            
    
    2. Search - O(n)
              - Searching means finding whether an element exists in the array.
              - To find an element, we may need to traverse the whole array.          
        Example - 30 - We need to traverse all elements in array. We may need to check every element one by one.     
                     - In worst case element is at the end or not present.
           
            int[] arr = {10, 20, 30, 40};

                int target = 30;
                for(int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
                   if(arr[i] == target) {
                     System.out.println("Found");
                    }
                 }

    3. Insertion - O(n)        
                 - Insertion means adding an element at a specific position.
                 - When inserting at middle or beginning, elements shift right.

        Example - [10,20,30,40] -Insert 15 at index 1 - [10,15,20,30,40]

    4. Delete - O(n) 
              - Deletion means removing an element.    
              - Deleting requires shifting elements left.
        Example - [10,20,30,40] - Delete 20 -[10,30,40]






